Fractional Brownian motion (fBm) is a process introduced by Kolmogorov [41], and employed by Mandelbrot [42]. fBm is a Gaussian process denoted typically by BH(t) depending on the Hurst index, H, located in 0 < H < 1. fBm has zero mean and covariance function defined asE[BH(t)BH(u)]=12[u2H+t2H−|t−u|2H],t,u∈[0,∞),when H=12;
