1/2(t) is a standard Wiener process or Brownian motion. Some interesting properties of fBm including self-similarity, being centered Gaussian process, having stationary increments, homogeneity in time, being symmetric and so on may be seen in, e.g. [43], [44], [45], [46], [50].
